WEBVTT

00:00.375 --> 00:02.001
<i>Previously on</i>
<i>"Switched at Birth"...</i>

00:02.049 --> 00:03.522
I'm gonna need
an immigration lawyer.

00:03.554 --> 00:04.554
Even if I get you a lawyer

00:04.589 --> 00:05.689
and you get out,
you can't come back.

00:05.723 --> 00:07.290
I'm still the girl's father.

00:07.325 --> 00:08.458
You can't come back
with me. We're done.

00:08.492 --> 00:09.492
I have a 3:00.

00:09.527 --> 00:12.462
No. Come on.
Blow off work.

00:12.496 --> 00:14.197
- We'll take a nap together.
- ( Both chuckling )

00:14.232 --> 00:15.465
What exactly do you need?

00:15.499 --> 00:17.133
Interviews? Notes?

00:17.168 --> 00:18.268
For what?

00:18.302 --> 00:20.203
- Your book.
- Really?

00:22.000 --> 00:28.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:30.815 --> 00:31.982
Why didn't you tell me?

00:32.016 --> 00:33.617
Because I don't want
to get involved.

00:33.651 --> 00:36.519
This concerns my brother,
my best friend and Bay.

00:36.554 --> 00:37.654
You didn't think I should know?

00:37.688 --> 00:39.556
Well, he might
be able to stay if...

00:39.590 --> 00:43.560
- If?
-... if Angelo marries a U.S. citizen.

00:46.264 --> 00:48.231
<i>( Classical music playing )</i>

01:15.660 --> 01:17.594
- <i>( Music stops )</i>
<i>- Why are you doing this?</i>

01:22.600 --> 01:24.534
<i>( Alarm beeping )</i>

01:27.305 --> 01:28.471
( Deep sigh )

01:32.310 --> 01:34.110
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:34.145 --> 01:35.979
You okay?

01:36.013 --> 01:37.247
Yeah. I, uh,

01:37.281 --> 01:40.283
just had a weird dream.

01:41.819 --> 01:42.953
You wanna grab some breakfast?

01:43.020 --> 01:43.987
I can't.

01:44.021 --> 01:48.558
I promised Kathryn
I would help set up.

01:48.592 --> 01:50.460
Bay's coming home today.

01:50.494 --> 01:52.429
( Upbeat guitar music playing )

01:56.534 --> 01:57.701
Oh! Ha ha ha!

01:57.735 --> 01:59.469
Ugh!

01:59.503 --> 02:00.503
( Whooping )

02:00.538 --> 02:02.539
Kennish beats Vasquez

02:02.573 --> 02:05.208
again!

02:05.242 --> 02:07.544
I think that Kennish
is conveniently forgetting

02:07.578 --> 02:10.013
about Vasquez's nine-day

02:10.047 --> 02:11.982
winning streak
of mid-July.

02:12.016 --> 02:13.283
Toby: <i>I beat you!
Fair and square!</i>

02:13.317 --> 02:14.351
No way!

02:14.385 --> 02:15.986
- Hey!
- Hey!

02:16.020 --> 02:17.087
- What up, sibbies?
- Daphne: Welcome home!

02:17.121 --> 02:18.121
Thank you.

02:18.155 --> 02:19.289
How was the galapagos?

02:19.323 --> 02:21.825
Or how were the galapagos?

02:21.859 --> 02:23.026
Muy bien, gracias.

02:23.060 --> 02:24.227
I brought back galapagifts.

02:24.261 --> 02:25.996
- Tob <i>sweet.</i>
<i>- Ooh.</i>

02:26.030 --> 02:27.797
So, uh, did you get bit

02:27.832 --> 02:28.965
by a blue-footed
booby?

02:29.000 --> 02:30.667
What's going on with your hair?

02:30.701 --> 02:31.868
Uh, I went island.

02:31.902 --> 02:34.637
And nothing you say
is gonna make me...

02:34.672 --> 02:35.839
Take it out.

02:35.873 --> 02:38.508
I'm sorry. My A.S.L.
has gotten rusty.

02:38.542 --> 02:39.642
I'm supposed
to invite you guys in.

02:39.677 --> 02:42.345
Uh, the welcome home party

02:42.380 --> 02:43.446
got bumped up a couple hours.

02:43.481 --> 02:45.415
Yeah, I thought that
John and Kathryn

02:45.449 --> 02:46.583
were picking you up
at 4:00.

02:46.617 --> 02:49.552
Our plane landed early,
so we just grabbed a cab.

02:51.355 --> 02:52.322
We?

02:54.458 --> 02:56.259
So we bonded over our hatred

02:56.293 --> 02:58.028
for the sun,
the ocean and sand.

02:58.062 --> 03:00.130
Well, I'm so glad we spent
four grand sending her.

03:00.164 --> 03:01.765
It was an enrichment program.

03:01.799 --> 03:03.800
I'm sure you learned
other things.

03:03.834 --> 03:04.901
Didn't you, Alex?

03:04.935 --> 03:06.636
<i>( Door opens )</i>
<i> Kathryn: Come on.</i>

03:06.670 --> 03:07.837
- ( Laughing )
- Hey! We heard you got back early.

03:07.872 --> 03:09.639
Kathryn: <i>Yeah.</i>

03:09.673 --> 03:11.508
Hi, uh, I'm Regina.

03:11.542 --> 03:12.642
- Hi.
- Adrianna.

03:12.676 --> 03:13.610
I'm Bay's grandmother.

03:13.644 --> 03:15.445
Oh cool.
You live here too?

03:15.479 --> 03:17.514
- Mm-hmm.
- And you're her...

03:17.548 --> 03:19.416
Aunt?

03:19.450 --> 03:20.450
Um...

03:20.484 --> 03:22.218
Not exactly.
( Nervous chuckle )

03:23.354 --> 03:25.321
Hey! I see
you met everyone.

03:25.356 --> 03:28.258
Ah, so this is Toby and Daphne,

03:28.292 --> 03:30.927
my brother and
sistery- type person.

03:30.961 --> 03:32.295
And this is everyone!

03:32.329 --> 03:34.864
So, everyone, this is Alex...

03:34.899 --> 03:36.066
My boyfriend.

03:36.100 --> 03:38.668
- Oh.
- Alex: Hi.

03:38.702 --> 03:40.670
- John: Wow.
- All: Hi.

03:40.704 --> 03:42.005
- Adriana: <i>Hi.</i>
<i>- Kathryn: Huh.</i>

03:42.355 --> 03:48.257
<font color="#ec14bd">Sync & corrections by <font color="#FFA500">wilson0804</font></font>
<font color="#ec14bd">www.Addic7ed.Com</font>

03:48.712 --> 03:49.746
( Whispering ) Maybe we
should give it more than

03:49.780 --> 03:51.648
14 minutes before we judge.

03:51.682 --> 03:53.750
Another boy? Is that
really what she needs?

03:53.784 --> 03:55.552
First this Liam,
the kid who enlisted,

03:55.586 --> 03:56.619
then Emmett, now this guy?

03:56.654 --> 03:57.887
I mean, come on,
she should take a break

03:57.922 --> 03:59.622
at some point.
Don't you think?

03:59.657 --> 04:02.559
And you're saying this
purely from a point

04:02.593 --> 04:03.560
of female empowerment,

04:03.594 --> 04:04.961
not as an overprotective dad?

04:04.995 --> 04:07.964
Okay. But the
feathers and the hair

04:07.998 --> 04:09.732
are just bad.

04:09.767 --> 04:10.967
- ( Sighs ) True.
- Yeah.

04:11.001 --> 04:12.735
( Normal voice ) Hey, you
guys, set the table.

04:12.770 --> 04:13.937
- Okay.
- Come on.

04:15.005 --> 04:16.706
So where does he go?

04:16.740 --> 04:17.874
St. Joseph's...

04:17.908 --> 04:21.678
Catholic, all boys, dangerous.

04:21.712 --> 04:24.681
( Chuckles ) Well, he
seems really nice.

04:24.715 --> 04:26.015
We had the greatest
time out there.

04:26.050 --> 04:28.785
We just laughed our way
through everything.

04:28.819 --> 04:30.787
So I hope this isn't awkward,

04:30.821 --> 04:33.690
but I promised Emmett
I'd give you a letter.

04:33.724 --> 04:34.858
I left it in your room.

04:36.026 --> 04:37.594
Thank you.

04:37.628 --> 04:39.596
He and I...

04:39.630 --> 04:40.997
I mean, I wasn't happy
about what happened,

04:41.031 --> 04:42.932
but we talked about it
a lot and...

04:42.967 --> 04:44.767
It's fine.

04:44.802 --> 04:45.935
Really.

04:45.970 --> 04:48.771
He was your friend first.

04:48.806 --> 04:50.607
I don't want to get involved,

04:50.641 --> 04:51.808
but you should know
that he is really...

04:51.842 --> 04:53.743
- Hey!
- I come bearing chips.

04:53.777 --> 04:55.712
Lots and lots o' chips.

04:55.746 --> 04:57.714
â™ª Excellent.

05:57.741 --> 05:59.976
It's so great having you home.

06:01.045 --> 06:02.545
And it seems... ooh.

06:03.647 --> 06:04.914
It seems like
you had a lot of fun.

06:04.949 --> 06:05.982
( Laughs )

06:06.016 --> 06:07.584
So honey,

06:07.618 --> 06:09.652
I invited Alex
to the book party.

06:09.687 --> 06:10.887
I hope that's okay.

06:10.921 --> 06:12.789
Right. Yeah
the book party.

06:12.823 --> 06:14.524
No, that's cool.

06:16.627 --> 06:17.827
Kathryn: Did you
like the cover art?

06:17.861 --> 06:20.530
When we had the photo
shoot with the babies,

06:20.564 --> 06:22.532
they gave me photo approval.

06:23.567 --> 06:25.535
Hon', you never
told me...

06:25.569 --> 06:26.903
You never told me

06:26.937 --> 06:28.705
if you like the book galleys.

06:28.739 --> 06:30.873
I know you were trying
not to be too connected

06:30.908 --> 06:31.941
when you were out there,

06:31.976 --> 06:33.710
so I didn't want
to push it...

06:33.744 --> 06:35.778
Oh! No, sorry,
I really really liked it.

06:35.813 --> 06:36.879
It was... it was honest.

06:36.914 --> 06:39.616
It's insightful.
It was funny even.

06:39.650 --> 06:41.718
Thank you.
Thank you very much.

06:43.921 --> 06:45.955
So are you still
in contact with Emmett?

06:47.591 --> 06:48.891
I never really got
a clear story

06:48.926 --> 06:50.960
- about what happened with you two.
- <i>( Knocks on door )</i>

06:50.995 --> 06:52.996
- Hey.
- Oh hi, Regina.

06:53.030 --> 06:54.631
Here's the stuff
for your bites.

06:55.666 --> 06:56.799
And I can pick you up some aloe

06:56.834 --> 06:57.767
when I go out,

06:57.801 --> 06:59.435
'cause that's really the best.

06:59.470 --> 07:01.537
Thanks. I heard
about your wrist.

07:01.572 --> 07:02.872
- That sucks!
- Yeah.

07:02.906 --> 07:05.441
Combination of signing
and cutting hair...

07:05.476 --> 07:07.410
Sort of a perfect storm
for inflamed tendons.

07:07.444 --> 07:10.313
The doctor says I just have
to rest it for a while.

07:11.348 --> 07:12.382
- Uh, Regina?
- Hmm?

07:12.416 --> 07:14.083
What's going on with Angelo?

07:15.119 --> 07:16.119
His hearing is in a week

07:16.153 --> 07:18.054
and he will present
everything to the court...

07:18.088 --> 07:19.255
Your letter, my letter,

07:19.290 --> 07:20.290
Daphne's letter.

07:20.324 --> 07:21.891
We wrote one too.

07:21.925 --> 07:23.826
Regina:
<i>Yes. Right. Thank you.</i>

07:23.861 --> 07:25.862
His lawyer thinks
that leaving suddenly

07:25.896 --> 07:28.731
would put undue hardship
on both you and Daphne.

07:28.766 --> 07:30.500
So he'll probably get to stay.

07:31.602 --> 07:33.469
I don't want to jinx anything,

07:33.504 --> 07:34.637
but things look good.

07:36.707 --> 07:38.508
Daphne: <i>I've been
cooking for my mom</i>

07:38.542 --> 07:40.443
and my grandma
since I was nine.

07:40.477 --> 07:42.445
I do this thing where I'll take

07:42.479 --> 07:44.380
an ingredient and I'll make

07:44.415 --> 07:46.115
like seven dishes with it,

07:46.150 --> 07:48.117
just to really get to know it.

07:49.153 --> 07:50.320
I see you're in high school.

07:50.354 --> 07:52.188
Yeah, it's not a problem.

07:52.222 --> 07:53.890
I took classes over the summer,

07:53.924 --> 07:55.825
so I'll get out at 2:00
every day this year.

07:55.859 --> 07:57.827
They're totally
supportive of it.

07:57.861 --> 07:59.696
I actually applied
for a bunch of jobs

07:59.730 --> 08:00.730
at the beginning of the summer,

08:00.764 --> 08:02.665
but I didn't get anything,

08:02.700 --> 08:04.701
so I figured I'd have a better
chance once all the college kids

08:04.735 --> 08:06.803
- went back to school.
- Well, you're right about that.

08:06.837 --> 08:08.805
We are looking.

08:08.839 --> 08:11.507
Can I ask what your accent is?

08:11.542 --> 08:13.376
It's so unusual.

08:14.545 --> 08:16.379
It's not Russian, is it?

08:17.481 --> 08:18.514
No.

08:18.549 --> 08:20.383
Swedish?

08:20.417 --> 08:21.384
Nuh-uh.

08:23.053 --> 08:24.954
I'm actually deaf.
It's a deaf accent.

08:24.988 --> 08:27.123
- Oh! I'm so sorry.
- It's really not a big deal.

08:27.157 --> 08:28.191
My dog is deaf.

08:28.225 --> 08:29.792
I promise you
I can do anything...

08:29.827 --> 08:31.861
You poor thing.

08:31.895 --> 08:34.097
( Loudly ) Thank you
so much for coming in.

08:34.131 --> 08:36.599
It... it's so nice
to meet you.

08:38.635 --> 08:39.736
It was nice to meet you too.

08:42.573 --> 08:44.440
John: <i>I just think the
whole thing is fantastic.</i>

08:44.475 --> 08:45.508
- I mean, come on!
- Honey.

08:45.542 --> 08:47.510
No ghostwriter!
Can you believe that?

08:47.544 --> 08:49.445
Every word, all her.

08:49.480 --> 08:50.546
I mean, I couldn't do that.

08:50.581 --> 08:51.514
Hmm.

08:51.548 --> 08:53.282
So I heard you have
a new lady friend.

08:53.317 --> 08:54.484
I do.

08:54.518 --> 08:56.619
The lovely Jenna has
been keeping me company.

08:56.653 --> 08:58.388
You sure bounced back fast.

08:59.523 --> 09:01.190
Well, it's not like

09:01.225 --> 09:02.358
Simone and I were
written in the stars

09:02.393 --> 09:03.426
or anything.

09:03.460 --> 09:06.095
Those would be some
pretty messed up stars.

09:07.297 --> 09:08.965
I'm actually surprised that

09:08.999 --> 09:10.366
you're in
a relationship so soon.

09:12.903 --> 09:14.937
I guess it just
goes to show you:

09:14.972 --> 09:16.105
Can't keep a good Kennish down.

09:16.140 --> 09:18.040
- No, sir.
- What?!

09:18.075 --> 09:20.176
- Ah!
- ( Both chuckling )

09:24.047 --> 09:26.816
So, nobody's tarred
and feathered you yet.

09:26.850 --> 09:28.851
I know. I guess
I thought people

09:28.886 --> 09:30.019
would be more judgmental.

09:30.053 --> 09:31.821
I think Kathryn did
a really good job

09:31.855 --> 09:32.889
explaining your side
of the story.

09:33.924 --> 09:34.957
She did.

09:37.628 --> 09:38.694
He seems like a good guy.

09:38.729 --> 09:39.695
<i>He is.</i>

09:41.532 --> 09:42.532
It's been interesting for me

09:42.566 --> 09:44.467
living with such
a solid couple.

09:44.501 --> 09:45.535
It certainly wasn't my model.

09:45.569 --> 09:47.203
( Chuckles ) Me neither.

09:47.237 --> 09:48.504
My parents stayed together
for me and my brother

09:48.539 --> 09:50.306
and shouldn't have.

09:50.340 --> 09:52.241
In fact, most marriages I know

09:52.276 --> 09:54.010
are terrible.

09:54.044 --> 09:55.978
I don't know about all of them.

09:56.013 --> 09:57.113
I prefer to be
in a relationship

09:57.147 --> 09:58.881
because both people choose to,

09:58.916 --> 10:01.150
not because getting out of it
would be a pain in the ass.

10:01.185 --> 10:02.985
So you don't
believe in it at all?

10:03.020 --> 10:04.086
Like, on principle?

10:04.121 --> 10:06.022
I just have never
understood the obsession

10:06.056 --> 10:07.790
with marriage
as an endgame, you know?

10:07.825 --> 10:08.925
It's a piece of paper.

10:10.928 --> 10:12.595
I'm glad we had
this conversation.

10:13.697 --> 10:15.264
Me too.

10:18.469 --> 10:20.536
"Oh, you're too
pretty to be deaf."

10:20.571 --> 10:22.171
Oh no way!

10:22.206 --> 10:23.573
That's the dumbest thing
I've ever heard.

10:23.607 --> 10:25.508
I wish I could just
keep it from them

10:25.542 --> 10:28.010
until I'm hired, but...

10:28.045 --> 10:30.112
I don't know. I don't feel
like that's very honest.

10:30.147 --> 10:31.180
Mm.

10:31.215 --> 10:33.316
How many interviews
have you had?

10:33.350 --> 10:34.851
12.

10:34.885 --> 10:36.185
Once they find out I'm deaf,

10:36.220 --> 10:38.087
it's basically over.

10:38.121 --> 10:40.056
Why don't you just ask my mom?

10:40.090 --> 10:41.891
I mean, she's got
connections everywhere.

10:41.925 --> 10:44.594
- No.
- Oh, that's a great idea.

10:44.628 --> 10:46.662
She got your mother
a job at Geraldo's.

10:46.697 --> 10:48.564
I want to get this on my own,

10:48.599 --> 10:49.799
not from someone

10:49.833 --> 10:51.434
begging them to take me on

10:51.468 --> 10:52.435
like some charity case.

10:52.469 --> 10:53.569
Yeah, but,

10:53.604 --> 10:55.338
you're qualified, right?
I mean, once you get

10:55.372 --> 10:57.473
in the door, you'll prove that.

10:59.243 --> 11:00.309
Gee, d-from me out there?
Kept a-( Laughs )Thing

11:00.344 --> 11:01.544
well, the good news is

11:01.578 --> 11:03.446
is my mom wrote
a whole book about it,

11:03.480 --> 11:04.514
so you can get caught up.

11:04.548 --> 11:06.449
"As a toddler, Bay was feisty,

11:06.483 --> 11:08.017
funny and fearless."

11:08.051 --> 11:09.352
Hmm.

11:09.386 --> 11:11.287
"It's true, she looked different
than the rest of us... "

11:11.321 --> 11:13.256
You know what? You don't
have to read it out loud.

11:13.290 --> 11:15.958
Just to yourself
is... is fine.

11:15.993 --> 11:17.827
It says you wet your
bed until you were 12.

11:17.861 --> 11:18.794
It says what?

11:20.230 --> 11:21.831
Oh. You're hilarious.

11:21.865 --> 11:24.834
You know what? I am gonna
go get more hummus. Enjoy.

11:24.868 --> 11:25.835
Who's Emmett?

11:25.869 --> 11:28.004
Uhh...

11:28.038 --> 11:29.705
Excuse me?

11:29.740 --> 11:31.674
"He rode up on his motorcycle

11:31.708 --> 11:33.643
looking like
a deaf James Dean."

11:34.711 --> 11:36.445
Sounds pretty hot.
Can I meet him?

11:38.549 --> 11:39.649
Could I see that?

11:44.521 --> 11:46.289
Uh, could you just
excuse me for like

11:46.323 --> 11:47.223
half a second?

11:53.096 --> 11:55.131
There's more if you need it.

11:55.165 --> 11:57.099
All right.

11:57.134 --> 11:59.235
You wrote about Emmett?

11:59.269 --> 12:01.137
Honey, the motorcycle
was the first thing

12:01.171 --> 12:02.872
that Regina and I argued about.

12:02.906 --> 12:04.974
Plus, he's Daphne's
best friend.

12:05.008 --> 12:06.909
I didn't write anything
about the two of you,

12:06.944 --> 12:09.612
'cause I knew you'd be
touchy about it, so...

12:10.781 --> 12:11.747
Did you even read the book?

12:13.784 --> 12:15.284
No.

12:15.319 --> 12:16.485
Why didn't you read it?

12:16.520 --> 12:18.254
You know how hard
I worked on it.

12:18.288 --> 12:19.322
I... I was busy.

12:19.356 --> 12:21.190
I had homework.
They made us do assignments.

12:22.526 --> 12:25.094
- I'm sorry.
- And why in the world

12:25.128 --> 12:26.395
wouldn't you tell
Alex anything?

12:26.430 --> 12:28.164
Mom, do you know
how nice it was

12:28.198 --> 12:30.232
to not be the girl
who was switched at birth

12:30.267 --> 12:32.168
just for a few weeks?

12:32.202 --> 12:35.871
It was a lie, but it was
still pretty awesome.

12:35.906 --> 12:37.873
Well, that's fine. But if you
couldn't be bothered to read

12:37.908 --> 12:39.875
the book, then you
can't complain about it.

12:39.910 --> 12:43.512
I didn't realize that you were
going to be writing about him.

12:44.681 --> 12:46.215
Honey,

12:46.249 --> 12:49.151
Emmett's a part of our story.

12:49.186 --> 12:51.420
I'm sorry,
but I can't erase that.

13:00.921 --> 13:02.688
John:
<i>Yeah. Big smile.</i>

13:02.723 --> 13:03.856
- All: Cheese.
- I think we got it.

13:03.890 --> 13:04.924
- Jaw's hurting.
- Oh!

13:04.958 --> 13:06.459
- Oh, I think...
- That's a nice picture!

13:06.493 --> 13:07.526
- That's fantastic.
- It sure is.

13:07.561 --> 13:08.794
You will thank me
for taking these pictures.

13:08.829 --> 13:10.496
They're not even
listening to me.

13:12.432 --> 13:13.566
Mom?

13:13.600 --> 13:14.634
Anything yet?

13:14.668 --> 13:16.602
