17:13.440 --> 17:14.440
Hey, good to see you.

17:19.512 --> 17:22.248
Bay. Bay.

17:22.281 --> 17:24.215
Bay, please.
Please. Wait.

17:24.251 --> 17:25.384
Can we talk for like a second?

17:27.087 --> 17:29.088
I'm really extremely sorry

17:29.122 --> 17:30.322
about everything.

17:30.357 --> 17:32.892
And I just wanted you
to know that I think

17:32.926 --> 17:35.728
that you and Emmett
were a great couple.

17:35.762 --> 17:37.029
And...

17:37.063 --> 17:38.831
I don't think that
one mistake should

17:38.865 --> 17:39.932
ruin that, you know?

17:41.868 --> 17:43.769
Okay. I get it.
You're gonna ignore me,

17:43.803 --> 17:44.803
and that's fine,

17:44.838 --> 17:47.406
but we go to a small school,

17:47.440 --> 17:48.641
we can't really
avoid each other.

17:48.675 --> 17:50.442
Then maybe you
should switch schools.

17:51.611 --> 17:53.512
- I can't do that.
- Why not?

17:54.648 --> 17:57.116
- Because I can't.
- Why not?

17:57.150 --> 17:59.118
Because I go here.

17:59.152 --> 18:00.986
Then don't.

18:01.021 --> 18:02.388
Don't go here anymore.

18:02.422 --> 18:04.256
- Bay...
- Look, you're a smart girl.

18:04.291 --> 18:06.191
You can figure this out.
Just go home,

18:06.226 --> 18:08.027
tell your parents
you want to transfer

18:08.061 --> 18:09.862
or something...
I really don't care.

18:09.896 --> 18:11.730
You want to do something
to make this better?

18:11.765 --> 18:14.033
Don't be in my world anymore.

18:14.067 --> 18:16.001
<i>( Bell rings )</i>

18:27.614 --> 18:29.448
You're Jeff Reycraft.

18:29.516 --> 18:31.684
Chef.
You call me chef.

18:31.718 --> 18:33.452
Chef. Right.

18:33.486 --> 18:36.288
I didn't think the interview
would be with you.

18:36.323 --> 18:37.456
I love your menu.
I've... I've never

18:37.490 --> 18:39.258
actually eaten here,
but I've studied it

18:39.292 --> 18:40.392
and, of course,
I've read about you...

18:40.427 --> 18:42.127
Get a jacket, find a knife,

18:42.162 --> 18:43.963
ask someone where
we keep the vegetables.

18:43.997 --> 18:45.331
Dice 30 onions in one
centimeter cubes...

18:45.365 --> 18:48.033
Not half a centimeter,
not two centimeters,

18:48.068 --> 18:49.201
one centimeter cubes.

18:52.939 --> 18:54.807
Yes? No?
You don't speak English?

18:54.841 --> 18:58.077
Sorry. I just thought
this would be an interview.

18:58.111 --> 19:00.679
Oh yeah, usually it is,
but your mom apparently knows

19:00.714 --> 19:03.482
someone really important,
so you're hired.

19:05.885 --> 19:07.853
"Thank you, chef."

19:07.887 --> 19:09.355
Thank you, chef.

