what haricots verts are,

22:36.298 --> 22:37.865
- <i>don't you?</i>
<i>- I'm sorry.</i>

22:37.900 --> 22:39.100
- I'm must have misunderstood...
- <i>She'll fix it.</i>

22:39.134 --> 22:41.002
We'll fix it.

22:41.036 --> 22:42.804
Uh, Daphne. They're
in the refrigerator.

22:42.838 --> 22:43.838
Cook: <i>Behind you.</i>

22:43.872 --> 22:45.740
- Behind you.
- Whoa!

22:45.774 --> 22:48.609
Oh my goodness.
I'm so sorry.

22:48.644 --> 22:50.778
I didn't know you were there.
I'm sorry.

22:50.813 --> 22:53.548
Just get out of here.
Out!

22:55.884 --> 22:57.618
It's trash.
Throw it away.

23:02.591 --> 23:04.258
Hey, what's for dinner tonight?

23:04.293 --> 23:05.526
I was hoping
for some of that baked ziti.

23:05.561 --> 23:08.196
I thought we'd just fend
for ourselves tonight.

23:08.230 --> 23:09.497
I have to answer
a bunch of emails,

23:09.531 --> 23:12.000
and I didn't have
time to stop at the store,

23:12.034 --> 23:13.368
- so...
- Oh.

23:15.104 --> 23:17.105
- What?
- Nothing.

23:18.207 --> 23:19.807
Say it.

23:20.843 --> 23:22.910
I like that we have
dinner together.

23:22.945 --> 23:24.879
And?

23:24.913 --> 23:27.749
And I don't know,
Kathryn. You know?

23:27.783 --> 23:29.617
I love our traditions, okay.

23:29.651 --> 23:31.386
I love that we take
pictures of the kids

23:31.420 --> 23:32.387
on their first day of school,

23:32.421 --> 23:34.255
and make peanut butter pancakes

23:34.289 --> 23:35.523
for their birthdays.

23:35.557 --> 23:38.426
And that I take
care of everything.

23:38.494 --> 23:40.161
Now wait a second.

23:40.195 --> 23:42.296
I'm not just some caveman.

23:42.331 --> 23:44.198
Not at all.
It's nice having

23:44.233 --> 23:46.167
someone take care of things.

23:46.201 --> 23:47.802
I would like it too.

23:47.836 --> 23:48.936
I take care of things.

23:48.971 --> 23:50.872
I mean, I did this summer.

23:50.906 --> 23:52.840
- ( Chuckles )
- <i>I did! I mean, you know,</i>

23:52.875 --> 23:53.941
more than normal.

23:56.011 --> 23:58.713
Look, I...

23:58.747 --> 24:02.350
The book took a lot of
time and commitment

24:02.384 --> 24:03.551
from you, from me,
from the kids,

24:03.585 --> 24:07.355
and I'm very proud
of what you did.

24:08.557 --> 24:11.426
<i>But I thought that when
the book was done...</i>

24:11.460 --> 24:14.095
Things would go back
to the way they were.

24:14.129 --> 24:15.229
Yeah.

24:17.232 --> 24:20.068
Honey, I got a lot of stuff
coming up in the next few months.

24:20.102 --> 24:23.871
I have book signings
and publicity and...

24:23.906 --> 24:27.675
When the book's over,
I'm gonna do something else.

24:29.545 --> 24:30.812
This isn't the end,

24:30.846 --> 24:32.380
it's the beginning.

24:33.515 --> 24:35.249
Okay.

24:37.286 --> 24:38.286
Is it?

24:40.122 --> 24:41.222
I'll get there.

24:43.492 --> 24:45.393
I hope so.

24:57.840 --> 24:58.873
Hi.

24:58.907 --> 25:01.976
I finished with
the <i>haricots verts.</i>

25:02.010 --> 25:03.644
I need turnips,
carrots and kale.

25:03.679 --> 25:05.847
- Turnips need to be scrubbed and peeled...
- Could you...

25:05.881 --> 25:07.715
I'm sorry I had
to interrupt, but

25:07.749 --> 25:09.650
could you please look at
me when you're talking,

25:09.685 --> 25:10.785
so I could read your lips?

25:13.622 --> 25:16.657
No, I cannot.

25:16.692 --> 25:18.459
- But...
- This is a kitchen.

25:18.494 --> 25:21.262
Not just a kitchen...
It's my kitchen.

25:21.296 --> 25:22.630
I am responsible,
not just for the food

25:22.664 --> 25:25.266
that comes out of it, but for all
the human beings who work in it.

25:25.300 --> 25:27.101
There are very large
knives in here.

25:27.136 --> 25:29.370
Boiling pots of water. If you
can't hear someone behind you,

25:29.404 --> 25:31.105
and you bump into
a guy holding a vat...

25:31.140 --> 25:32.140
I'm really sorry about that.

25:32.174 --> 25:33.141
Listen.

25:35.377 --> 25:38.279
I'm sure you grew up being told you
could do anything you wanted, right?

25:38.313 --> 25:40.114
- Yes.
- Well, that's good.

25:40.149 --> 25:41.849
You had good parents.

25:41.884 --> 25:43.117
But now I'm going
to tell you the truth.

25:43.152 --> 25:45.786
You can't do everything.

25:45.821 --> 25:47.655
I can't be a jockey
because I'm 6'4".

25:47.689 --> 25:50.825
My sister can't be a Broadway star
because she don't sing so good.

25:50.859 --> 25:52.460
We weren't meant
to do everything.

25:52.494 --> 25:54.662
That's why God created
each of us <i>different.</i>

25:57.332 --> 26:00.535
I heard you were deaf, I
didn't know what to expect.

26:00.569 --> 26:02.170
I said, "let's give it a try,"

26:02.204 --> 26:05.306
but now you're in my kitchen.

26:05.340 --> 26:08.309
And the fact is,
it's a problem.

26:08.343 --> 26:11.979
The law says that I have to accommodate
you to the best of my ability,

26:12.014 --> 26:14.248
so if you want to stay...

26:16.051 --> 26:18.052
Go wash dishes.

26:18.086 --> 26:19.720
Can't do much damage there.

26:27.743 --> 26:29.783
Okay. So he's getting out
in a couple of days.

26:29.823 --> 26:33.559
- Yeah.
- ...And you call him "Angelo"?

26:33.593 --> 26:35.761
Well, that's his name.

26:35.796 --> 26:37.797
But he's your dad.

26:37.831 --> 26:41.567
Yeah. But, uh,
my dad is...

26:41.601 --> 26:43.369
My dad.

26:43.403 --> 26:45.638
And you looked for his
car in a junkyard,

26:45.672 --> 26:47.673
but all you found
was a guitar pick

26:47.708 --> 26:50.176
that belonged to a gay dj named.

26:50.210 --> 26:51.143
Angelo Sorrento.

26:51.178 --> 26:52.378
No no.
The guitar pick

26:52.412 --> 26:55.381
belonged to my Angelo
and the gay Angelo...

26:55.415 --> 26:57.149
Sorrento was, ah...

26:57.184 --> 26:59.018
- I'm... I'm sorry, I...
- Oh no. ( Chuckles )

26:59.052 --> 27:00.086
No, it's fine.
It's just, I...

27:00.120 --> 27:01.921
It's hard for me
to follow sometimes.

